race.comment: GIAPPONESE (5) was well supported on resumption when attacking the line strongly for a narrow second over 1400m at Grafton. Has the upside to go on with it here from the awkward barrier. ADEQUATE EZE (3) is a lightly raced gelding improving with racing. Warmed up late when second in a small field over 1415m at Ballina. Can race a little closer from the draw and is expected to take a hand in the finish. SKIEDA (10) resumes after disappointing last time in work. Fitted with the two searching trials and primed for a first-up victory. BLIGHTYS HOPE (7) returns from a lengthy break. Failed to fire in her first campaign and expected to have matured. Given the one 1000m trial at the Gold Coast. Improver in this weaker race.
